---
description: Always apply the Workspace OS workspace operating guide.
alwaysApply: true
---

This project is a Workspace OS workspace.

Before doing business work:
- Read @AGENTS.md and @INDEX.md.
- Treat @AGENTS.md as the workspace operating guide, not a duplicate agent profile.
- For business work, follow @agents/workspace-chief.md as the Workspace Chief coordinator.
- Ground work in @{{DOCS_ROOT}}/business-profile.md.
- Apply @_workspace_setup_docs/skills/apply-workspace-struct.md whenever creating, moving, or editing artifacts.
- Route repeatable workflow or preference changes to @agents/sub-agents/skill-librarian.md.
- When the user provides raw notes or points to a loose notes file, process it automatically:
  create the standard folder, preserve raw input under a `raw/` archive subfolder, write the summary
  in the main folder, remove the loose inbox copy after archiving it, update indexes, and then report
  the created paths. Do not give an option menu in place of filing the notes.
- When the user asks for insights, recommendations, prioritization, scope, trade-offs, or what
  to do next, create an outcome artifact under `{{DOCS_ROOT}}/outcomes/`, update the outcomes index,
  and reply with only a short handoff plus the file path.
- When the user asks about UX, brand and delivery trade-offs, accessibility, metrics, experiments, plans,
  release planning, exec updates, launch notes, client summaries, or client alignment, route the
  work through the Workspace Chief and create the durable artifact under the matching `{{DOCS_ROOT}}/` lane:
  `brand-and-delivery/`, `metrics/`, `plans/`, or `client-comms/`.

Always keep indexes current:
- Any file or folder created, moved, renamed, or meaningfully edited must update the nearest INDEX.md in the same change.
- If a new top-level area is created, also update the root @INDEX.md.
- Do not leave stale links or undocumented new artifacts.

Keep documentation alive:
- Update @{{DOCS_ROOT}}/business-profile.md when the business, audience, goal, positioning, or strategy changes.
- If another business doc should be updated and the source is clear, route the work through the Workspace Chief to the right specialist.
- If the owner wants to teach the workspace a new process, route through the Workspace Chief to the skill-librarian.
- When adding, updating, merging, or removing a skill, also update `business-skills/START_HERE.md`,
  `business-skills/INDEX.md`, `agents/sub-agents/INDEX.md`, the matching sub-agent file, and Workspace Chief routing.
  Remove orphaned sub-agents or stale skill links in the same change.
- When the owner provides reusable templates or examples for a workflow, put blank formats under
  `business-practices/templates/`, examples/style samples under `business-practices/references/`, update the relevant index,
  and connect the relevant skill to those files.
- Do not overwrite raw notes; create summaries, decisions, offer briefs, and documentation as new artifacts.
